<p>I got problem solving 'reverseBytes' in cs:app datalab.</p>  <p>i have to make code that returns reversed byte order.</p>  <p><em>example : input=0x123456, returns=0x563412</em></p>  <p>when i used my code, it can't take a score..</p>  <pre><code>int reverseBytes(int x) {   int mask=0xff;   int byte1=x&gt;&gt;24;   int byte2=(x&gt;&gt;16)&amp;mask;   int byte3=(x&gt;&gt;8)&amp;mask;   int byte4=x&amp;mask;   int result=(byte4&lt;&lt;24)|(byte3&lt;&lt;16)|(byte2&lt;&lt;8)|(byte1);    return result; } </code></pre>  <p>but, when i used other people's code, it takes a score.</p>  <pre><code>int reverseBytes(int x) {   int t2=~(0xff&lt;&lt;24);   int s1=(0xff&lt;&lt;16)+0xff;   int s2=0xff&lt;&lt;8;   int s3=(s2&lt;&lt;16)+s2;   int temp=(x&amp;s1)&lt;&lt;8|((x&amp;s3)&gt;&gt;8&amp;t2);   int q1=(0xff&lt;&lt;8)+0xff;   int q2=q1&lt;&lt;16;   int temp2=(temp&amp;q1)&lt;&lt;16|((temp&amp;q2)&gt;&gt;16&amp;(~q2));    return temp2; } </code></pre>  <p>i don't know why my code can't works.. i tested my code and other people's code. but i can't find difference between my code's result and another code's result. please help me..</p>